      "span_text": "There is little evidence that having an abnormal radiograph (including signs of disc degeneration) at the time the acute injury affects the outcome.  Thus, in the vast majority of whiplash claimants, the various, commonly identified radiological abnormalities do not correlate with symptoms and merely represent the background prevalence of such findings in the general population."
